org.hl7.types.impl
Class CDimpl

java.lang.Object
  org.hl7.types.impl.ANYimpl
      org.hl7.types.impl.CDimpl
All Implemented Interfaces:
ANY, CD
public final class CDimpl
extends ANYimpl
implements CD

Minimal implementation of CD as a model we can use for all other type. This one is only used to convey NULL values. Again, we have static values of it, so we don't create so many objects in a running program.

equal

public BL equal(ANY that)
Description copied from class: ANYimpl
We require that all inheritors of ANYimpl have their own equal function for all of its compatible types.

The equals function is not a no-brainer. THINK!

Equal must first test for type compatibility (not necessarily type-equality.) Be sure to test for the interface, not the implementation type, as the same type may have different implementations.
